data.description: Welcome to a true gem of the past, a meticulously preserved Craftsman-style home that promises a unique blend of timeless elegance and modern comfort. Nestled in a prime location, this 2-bedroom, 1-bathroom residence is a beautifully maintained time capsule, with its roots dating back to 1913. As you step inside, you'll be transported to an era of craftsmanship, where every detail tells a story. With a generous 1600 square feet of living space, this home offers a spacious environment that exudes warmth and character. The refinished original wood floors add a touch of authenticity and charm that's impossible to replicate. The cellar and unfinished attic space, are perfect for your imagination and plans. The built-ins throughout the house not only provide practical storage but also showcase the intricate craftsmanship of the era. The kitchen nook is a perfect spot for enjoying your morning coffee, while the wrap-around porch invites you to sit back and relax as you take in the picturesque surroundings. The large, well-manicured yard is a canvas for your creativity, offering a peaceful retreat or a space for entertaining guests. But that's not all this property has to offer. With a convenient carport and RV parking, you'll have ample space for all your vehicles and toys. Additionally, there's a single-car garage that has the potential to be converted into an Accessory Dwelling Unit (ADU), providing endless possibilities for extra living space, a home office, or a rental income opportunity. The location of this home is equally impressive. Situated close to the University of La Verne, the local high school, downtown, the Pomona Fairplex, and major freeways, you'll have all the amenities and conveniences within easy reach. Whether you're seeking dining, entertainment, or cultural experiences, this home's location offers a world of possibilities. This Craftsman-style residence is not just a house; it's a piece of California history waiting for someone who appreciates the timeless beauty of yesteryears while enjoying the comforts of today. If you're ready to own a piece of the past, this property is your perfect opportunity. Don't miss the chance to make this piece of history your own.
